reviews.text:
Nice view and delicious food. Roasted goose and the crispy rice in supreme lobster broth were my favourite! Mom loves their stir-fry sole fish fillets and steamed red date pudding. 

Service was good, service staff Oscar was professional and attentive. 

Recommend!

Good food but need more staff

we booked a table for dinner in advance and was put in the seats right by the entrance. had a nice view so we said ok. But it turns out the staff were very busy and being so far away meant the service was very average. the staff were nice but just not there when we needed them.

we ordered 2 starters. the tofu was very good. and 3 main dishes. 2 of the main dishes arrived together but the 3rd (the vegetables dish) had not arrived despite us almost finishing the others... we had to wait for when we could locate some staff and they chased it up for us. not the level of service you would expect to be honest and ruined the dinner a little bit.

nice setting and environment, good quality food but service let it down. free parking if spending over a certain amount.

High end Cantonese food. However the restaurant has low ceiling so it's very noisy. Otherwise the dishes are mostly good. Especially like the eel and the lemon crispy prawns. The lobster soup rice is also very tasty. The only disappointing dish is the braised pork spare rib.
A rather good dim sum place! Great food, amazing service and spectacular view of the harbour. You do pay for it.
Good food good view. Up to the standard of a 5 star hotel experience.

reviews.text: Great views but music was too loud and food is overpriced on happy hour menu. Staff comes over when you don't need them and nowhere to be found when you do. Go for the views but service and food is nothing special.

Incredible bar in Kerry Hotel. Great indoor atmosphere which blends relaxing seating and traditional, oakwood bar decor with low lighting. Outside there is a garden terrace with fountains and mood lighting, in addition to an utterly stunning view of Hong Kong. The drinks are very good as well, as one can get specially mixed cocktails by taking a bit to the bartenders. Pricing is lower than any proper bar on Hong Kong Island, but at a very high level of luxury. Highly recommended!
Very nice bar with both indoor and outdoor areas. The outdoor area has 270 degree panoramic view of the harbour.
Fantastic signature cocktails, good and friendly service, strongly recommended for one or two drinks after a long day of meetings and sightseeing in Hong Kong.
Red.Sugar.is in the Kerry Hotel.it has a beautiful terrace overlooking the harbour. The views are wonderful and the drinks are good. They do have a wonderful brunch here.

reviews.text: I really cannot say enough good things about The Kerry. Everything was absolutely perfect and we had such an incredible time here. The room was BEAUTIFUL and clean, and the staff was super friendly and unbelievably accommodating when we needed them a few times. Also, the Big Bay Cafe was SO GOOD!!! We had breakfast there every morning and did dinner there once; the food was impeccably delicious and the staff/service was on point. In fact it was so good that if I'm ever back in HK and not staying at the Kerry Hotel I would not hesitate to swing by the Big Bay Cafe for a meal or two!

Decent hotel and good food in room service. Some experiences were very bureaucratic - for instance I asked for a 30 min extension on room checkout and the lady was insistent that that cannot happen. At 1115 pm, we were told by the concierge that the bar is closed and last orders are taken. however when we went there, the bar was more than happy to accommodate us and get us food. So the quality of service greatly depended on who you spoke to

It's my favourite hotel and I travel a lot. This time I brought my 4 kids and wife who loved it! The views are magnificent as are the facilities. We used the Club Lounge which is highly recommended. Location is great with MTR a 5 minute walk.

Club room. Free room upgrade for my birthday. Room comes with club access - great evening  cocktails and amazing breakfast. Room and pool superb. Staff very helpful and hard working. This is our 3rd stay at Kerry and every stay is better than the last! Keep up the great work!

Nice overall. Housekeeping was.helpful to deliver the items promptly everyday. Receptionist were quick and fast.
2nd day make up room was left with only 1 towel left but it wasn't a big deal. Overall great stay!
